snippet.title: FIRST CLASS on Africa‚Äôs SAFARI TRAIN (4 Nights, 88hrs!)
snippet.description:
Welcome onboard one of the World‚Äôs Greatest Rail Journeys! This is Rovos Rail: First Class on Africa‚Äôs Safari Train (4 Nights, 88hrs)! 

Watch this video before booking Rovos Rail‚Äôs journey from Pretoria to Victoria Falls!! On our journey through incredible landscapes and national parks, we‚Äôll spend four days and four nights on Africa‚Äôs most luxurious train! We‚Äôll travel through South Africa and across Zimbabwe by luxury train!

Rovos Rail‚Äôs First Class Train should be at the top of your travel bucket list. In this video, we‚Äôll leave Pretoria, just outside Johannesburg at 6:15pm on our first day. We‚Äôll head north, into Zimbabwe where, four nights later, we‚Äôll arrive at Victoria Falls, one of the Seven Wonders of the World. Along the way, we‚Äôll travel in a First Class train car in the Deluxe Suite with every amenity you can imagine (and some First Class Luxuries guaranteed to surprise you!).

Onboard the Deluxe Suite experience, we‚Äôll have our own dedicated hostess to take care of our every need, a HUGE room with massively comfortable beds, and delicious, five star food.

Our room is in the middle category of Suites on the train. We‚Äôll also show you around the entire train, including the lounge cars, dining cars, and - my favorite - the observation car!

We even had the opportunity to get out and explore two incredible national parks along the way: Matobo National Park (Zimbabwe‚Äôs oldest national park) and Hwange National Park (Zimbabwe‚Äôs largest national park). In both, we‚Äôll have some pretty wild animal encounters, making this a true Train Safari

You‚Äôll see the sights, the food, and gain insight into what it‚Äôs like to travel on this incredible First Class Safari Train: Rovos Rail!
